Watching Eddie Hall doing track runs and Ninja Warrior courses is absolutely incredible because he is incredibly heavy but has pretty much infinite grip strength so once he gets a hold of something he simply never lets go.

If you're not watching his channel ur missing out A LOT

His show is literally some of the best entertainment online, its fascinating to see the best lifter of our age forced to do obstacle adventure courses

Eddie is very much a natural athlete, u can see him adapt and study the challenges in real time, and develop personalized strats

I've shared my dislike of casual powerlifting (too much injuries, not that useful), but *very high* level powerlifting is fascinating to see, it requires some real skills

Like you can see that Eddie is literally competitive in all physical activities, he BTFOs a lot of athletes

Watch his most recent video and just look at the part 2/3ds into the video that consists of hanging on his grip strength, he's literally unstoppable Absolutely love the big lad, was neutral about him before watching his channel, but he's so precious <3 youtube.com/watch?v=GNHBTrvs‚Ä¶
